# 👨‍🏫 Teacher Topic Management API Documentation

## 📍 Base URL

```bash id="p2k8vn"
http://localhost:5000/teacher
```

---

# 🧭 Overview

This module allows **teachers** to:

* Create topics
* Update topics
* Delete topics
* View their draft topics

🔐 All routes require authentication and **teacher role**.

---

# 🔐 Authentication & Authorization

All endpoints require:

```http id="q7m3xs"
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN
```

### ✅ Access Control

* User must be authenticated (valid JWT)
* User must have role: **teacher**

---

# 📝 1. Create Topic

## 🔗 Endpoint

```bash id="x9d4ru"
POST /teacher/create-topic
```

## 🔐 Auth Required

✅ Yes (Teacher only)

---

## 📥 Request Body

```json id="j2v6pk"
{
  "title": "AI-based Chatbot for Education",
  "description": "Develop a chatbot to assist students using NLP",
  "status": "draft"
}
```

> ℹ️ `status` can be:

* `"draft"` (default while editing)
* `"published"` (if ready)

---

## ✅ Response

```json id="r8y1tw"
{
  "message": "Topic created successfully",
  "topic_id": 1
}
```

---

